    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This collector-grade E46 M3 is a superlative example of BMW M-division engineering. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and a high-revving 8,000 RPM redline, delivering 333hp with surgical precision. The drivetrain is anchored by a crisp ZF 6-speed manual transmission and a factory-variable M differential lock for optimal torque distribution. This chassis has been meticulously preserved and mechanically optimized: the dual-VANOS system has been overhauled, rod bearings replaced preventatively, and the rear subframe reinforced to ensure structural integrity under high lateral loads. The suspension retains its original geometry and damping characteristics, offering the communicative handling and telepathic steering response the platform is celebrated for. With zero deferred maintenance and immaculate aesthetics, this vehicle represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated performance.",
